<h2>Mi ris, mi plours</h2>

<dl>
<dt>Mi ris, mi plours</dt>
<dd>Musiques des XIII&egrave;me et XIV&egrave;me si&egrave;cles<br>
Ensemble Faenza - Marco Horvat<br>
<i>Tabula Rasa TR01</i></dd>
</dl>

<h3>Contents:</h3>
<p><ol>
<li>Anon: Ave Gloriosa (motet; 2 voices)</li>
<li>Anon: Istampita Ghaetta (estampie; recorder, vielle, percussion)</li>
<li>Gautier de Coincy: Ma vi&egrave;le (chanson; voice, vielle)</li>
<li>Anon., Codex Faenza: De toutes flours (diminution after Machaut;
lute, vielle)</li>
<li>Machaut: Tel rit au main (complainte; recorder)</li>
<li>Machaut: Liement me deport (virelai; voice, citole, recorder,
vielle, percussion)</li>
<li>Anon., Codex Faenza: Che pena &egrave; questa (diminution after
Landini; recorder, 2 vielles)</li>
<li>Machaut: Dame, je weil endurer (virelai; voice, vielle)</li>
<li>Machaut: Ay mi! dame de valour (virelai, voice, vielle,
percussion)</li>
<li>Anon: Estampie (recorder, vielle)</li>
<li>Anon., Codex Rossi: Per tropo fede (ballata; recorder)</li>
<li>Anon: Non perch' i speri (ballate; recorder)</li>
<li>Anon., Codex Faenza: Honte, paour, doubtance (diminution after
Machaut; 2 vielles)</li>
<li>Anon., Laudario di Cortona: Amor dolce (laude; voice, citole,
percussion)</li>
<li>Machaut: Dame, ne regardes pas (ballade; 2 voices)</li>
<li>Anon: Chrominciamento di gioia (estampie; recorder, vielle,
percussion)</li>
</ol></p>

<p>Performers:  Marco Horvat (voice, citole, lute, vielle), Magali
Imbert (recorder, daf), Bruno Caillat (daf), Rafael Boulay (voice),
Maria-Carolina Concha (vielle)</p>

<p>Playing time: 63'</p>

<p>Recording dates: May &amp; October 1997 (Paris)</p>

<p>Information from Tony Reif.</p>

